Desc - Abstract: Medical News Visiting List, published 1892 by Lea Brothers & Co. Leather-bound physician’s pocket appointment book or notebook with gold stamping on outer flap, “containing an arranged visiting list with the usual accessories, dosage table, poisons and their antidotes, method of examination of urine, a comparative table of the different thermometers and scales, and a table of weights and measures, with also surgical directions as to certain operations, such as ligation of arteries, and a list of remedies for all the disorders commonly met with” (JAMA, 22 December, 1900).
